HEADWORD: Gluttony
<hw>Glut"ton*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Gluttonies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>glotonie</ets>,
OF. <ets>glotonie</ets>, <ets>gloutonnie</ets>.]</ety> <def>Excess in
eating; extravagant indulgence of the appetite for food;
voracity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their sumptuous <qex>gluttonies</qex>, and gorgeous feasts.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glycerate</ent>⟦br⟧
